Citation.sTitle: Ultrasonic speeds and isentropic compressibilities of {difurylmethane + (C1 C6) n-alkanol} binary mixtures at T = 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, and ultrasonic speeds of {difurylmethane + (methanol or ethanol or propan-1-ol or butan-1-ol or pentan-1-ol or hexan-1-ol)} binary mixtures have been measured over the entire composition range at T = 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure. Excess isentropic compressibility coefficient, excess ultrasonic speeds, and excess intermolecular free length, of each binary system were calculated and correlated by the Redlich-Kister equation. The results are discussed in terms of possible intermolecular interactions and structural effects.
